    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Chout [Charles Chordeau Johnson] to Mr. Paul Rockwell <date value="1916-10-02">Oct 2nd 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-10-02">Oct 2nd 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            Everything is going on
            about the same as when you
            left.
            </p><p>
            I am enclosing the discours [sic]
            of the Capt.
            </p><p>
            When you get through with
            your affairs in Paris come on
            back &amp; club around with us in
            Luxeuil.  You can do your work just
            as well here &amp; better than in
            Paris &amp; forget things with the
            crowd.
            </p><p>
            My best remembrances to Mrs.
            Weeks.
            </p><p>
            Hears how to Jim.  Paul
            sends best to all &amp; will write soon.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>As ever.</salute>
            
            <signed>Chout [Charles Chordeau Johnson]</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            <!-- [This letter is addressed to Mr. Paul Rockwell, 80 rue Boissiere, Paris.] -->
            
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
